text:
O God! Thou art my God alone;
My soul thirsts for Thee, like parched land.
In Thee, my heart finds its home;
My spirit finds solace in Thy hand.

In times of trouble, I call on Thee;
My Savior, my Refuge, my Redeemer, be.
In Thee, I find my peace and rest;
My hope, my joy, my eternal quest.

Thy love, O God, is like a river;
It flows from Thee, and never sever.
It quenches my thirst, and washes me clean;
It makes me new, and lifts me unseen.

